Description:
   Generate a sponsors.yml file for a given event.
   If the file already exists, adds the sponsor in the correct tier.
   If the sponsor already exists in the file, updates the existing sponsor record.
   Tiers can only be added on the first pass.

Example: Create a new sponsors.yml file for an event with the first sponsor added.
    bin/rails generate sponsors --event rails-world-2026 --tiers "Platinum,Gold,Silver,Sponsors,Members" \
      --name "App Signal" --website "https://www.appsignal.com" \
      --logo_url "https://rubyonrails.org/assets/images/logo-appsignal.svg" \
      --tier "Platinum"

    This will create:
        /data/rails-world/rails-world-2026/sponsors.yml

Example: Add a new sponsor to an existing sponsors.yml file
  bin/rails g sponsors --event rubyconf-austria-2026 --name "Teamtailor" --website "https://teamtailor.com/" \
    --tier "Gold Online" --logo_url "https://rubyconf.at/assets/images/sponsors/teamtailor.png"

Example: Update a sponsor's tier
  bin/rails g sponsors --event tropical-on-rails-2026 --name "Sponsor Name" --tier "Platinum"